## Set up OS
Start with Fedora 37. Run all updates.
sudo dnf group install "C Development Tools and Libraries" "Development Tools"

## Download ChromeOS kernel
https://www.dropbox.com/s/4b225bh5ax63n75/cros%20kernel.zip?dl=0

## Copy files
vmlinuz needs to go into /boot/vmlinuz-5.10.164-gddc0853e897c
tar xf modules-stable.tar.xz -C /lib/modules

## After build, install
sudo dracut --kver 5.10.164-gddc0853e897c initramfs-5.10.64-gddc0853e897c.img
sudo chmod +x /boot/vmlinuz-5.10.164-gddc0853e897c

## Update grub
sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg

## Note: updating grub will not add the custom kernel.
Add an entry in 40_custom or manually edit a boot line in grub to boot from the 5.10.64 kernel. 
